{"author":"butlers/refinery","created_at":"2026-03-06T14:36:24Z","id":1,"issue_id":"bu-olm","text":"## Reconciliation: Epic bu-95s — Scoped Refinery Test Runs\n\n### Epic Requirements (from bu-95s description)\n1. Detect which modules changed in MR branch vs main\n2. Run only the relevant test subset\n3. Fall back to full suite when changes touch shared code (conftest, fixtures, core utils)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement Coverage Checklist\n\n#### bu-c05: Diff-based changed-file detection — COVERED (merged to main: 07980b51)\n- [x] Function get_changed_files(branch, base) in changed_files.py\n- [x] Uses git diff --name-only with three-dot diff (base...branch)\n- [x] Handles renames via --no-renames (decomposed to delete+add)\n- [x] Handles deleted files (appear in diff output)\n- [x] Handles merge commits (three-dot diff isolates branch changes)\n\n#### bu-czr: Source-to-test mapping — COVERED (merged to main: 51e8a1c1)\n- [x] resolve_test_paths(changed_files) in source_test_map.py\n- [x] Direct module-to-test-dir via _PREFIX_MAP (24+ entries)\n- [x] Cross-cutting files trigger full suite via FULL_SUITE_TRIGGERS\n- [x] Non-Python changes excluded via _NO_TEST_PREFIXES\n- [x] Roster-specific mapping via _roster_test_paths()\n- [x] Deterministic sorted output\n\n#### bu-g4r: Scoped test runner — ON FEATURE BRANCH ONLY (7f88b5c6)\n- [x] plan_scoped_tests() + build_pytest_command() + run_scoped_tests()\n- [x] Preserves uv run pytest + --ignore=tests/test_db.py\n- [x] Reports scope and reasoning via ScopedTestPlan.report()\n- [x] CLI entry point (__main__)\n- [ ] NOT on main — only on feat/bu-4mb-tiered-pricing\n\n#### bu-k5t: Full-suite fallback — CODE STRANDED ON POLECAT BRANCH\n- [x] Implementation exists on polecat/obsidian/bu-k5t@mmewn1px with:\n  - FULL_SUITE_FALLBACK_ALLOWLIST (conftest.py, tests/conftest.py, src/butlers/core/, base.py, registry.py, pyproject.toml, migrations/)\n  - find_fallback_trigger() function\n  - Configurable fallback_allowlist parameter\n  - Clear per-file logging of trigger + matched pattern\n  - tests/conftest.py and registry.py added to FULL_SUITE_TRIGGERS\n- [ ] Branch was NEVER merged to main or feature branch. Bead closed prematurely.\n\n#### bu-5d8: pytest-xdist parallel execution — NOT OPERATIONAL\n- [ ] Bead closed \"with no code changes\" but -n auto is absent from:\n  - build_pytest_command() output\n  - CLAUDE.md test commands\n  - All test invocations in codebase\n\n---\n\n### Uncovered Requirements (new beads needed)\n\n1. **Merge bu-k5t fallback code** — The full-suite fallback allowlist is stranded on polecat/obsidian/bu-k5t@mmewn1px. Must be cherry-picked or re-implemented on main.\n\n2. **Integrate scoped runner into refinery patrol** — bu-g4r says \"Replace the refinery's full-suite pytest invocation with a scoped runner.\" The scoped_runner.py module exists as a library but nothing in the refinery patrol (mol-refinery-patrol) calls it. The refinery still uses its raw test_command variable. The scoped runner must be wired into the refinery's test execution step.\n\n3. **Enable pytest-xdist -n auto** — bu-5d8 was incorrectly closed. -n auto must be added to pytest invocations (both scoped and full-suite runs) in the scoped runner.\n"}
{"author":"butlers/polecats/obsidian","created_at":"2026-03-06T15:52:59Z","id":2,"issue_id":"bu-axm.4","text":"## Research: store_fact Bitemporal API Design\n\n### 1. store_fact() in storage.py — valid_at + temporal skip\n\n**Current state:** No `valid_at` parameter, no temporal awareness.\n\n**Required changes:**\n- Add `valid_at: datetime | None = None` to the signature (after existing keyword-only params)\n- Include `valid_at` in the INSERT (new column via migration)\n- **Supersession skip logic:** When `valid_at is not None`, bypass the existing-fact lookup entirely — do NOT check for existing active facts, just INSERT. This is the temporal skip: temporal facts coexist by design.\n- When `valid_at is None` (default), current supersession behavior is unchanged.\n\n**Key insight:** The supersession skip is controlled purely by whether `valid_at` is provided by the caller. No registry lookup needed at write time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Predicate registry — is_temporal flag\n\n**Decision: Informational only, not a runtime signal.**\n\nThe `predicate_registry` table (migration 005) lacks `is_temporal`. It needs to be added, but `store_fact` should NOT query the registry at write time to determine temporal behavior. Reasons:\n\n- **Performance:** Extra DB lookup on every store_fact call, for no behavioral benefit\n- **Correctness:** The spec's conditional is on `valid_at IS NULL vs IS NOT NULL`, not on predicate name. See spec lines 56-68.\n- **Registry role:** `is_temporal` in the registry is prompt-injection guidance for LLM extractors — it hints that when using a temporal predicate, include `valid_at`. It does not enforce runtime behavior.\n\n**Required migration (mem_007):**\n```sql\nALTER TABLE predicate_registry ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS is_temporal BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false;\nUPDATE predicate_registry SET is_temporal = true WHERE name IN ('meal_breakfast', 'meal_lunch', 'meal_dinner', 'meal_snack');\n```\n\n**Also needed (separate migration):** Add `valid_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL DEFAULT NULL` to the `facts` table, plus index on `(entity_id, scope, predicate, valid_at)` for temporal range queries.\n\n---\n\n### 3. memory_store_fact MCP tool in writing.py\n\n**Required changes:**\n- Add `valid_at: str | None = None` to `memory_store_fact()` function signature (ISO 8601 string from MCP callers)\n- Parse to `datetime` using `datetime.fromisoformat(valid_at)` before passing to `store_fact()`\n- Update `__init__.py` memory_store_fact tool registration to expose `valid_at` as an MCP parameter with description\n\n---\n\n### 4. Search/recall — valid_at range filtering\n\n**Decision: Add valid_at_from / valid_at_to to memory_search only.**\n\n`memory_recall` is a composite-scored open-ended retrieval for context injection — date range filtering doesn't fit its use case.\n\n**Required changes to search.py `search()` / `semantic_search()` / `keyword_search()`:**\n- Add `valid_at_from: datetime | None = None` and `valid_at_to: datetime | None = None`\n- When provided, add `AND (valid_at IS NULL OR valid_at BETWEEN $n AND $m)` to the facts SQL\n- (Only applied to the facts table, not episodes or rules)\n\n**Required changes to tools/reading.py `memory_search()`:**\n- Accept and pass through `valid_at_from` / `valid_at_to`\n\n**Required changes to `__init__.py` tool registration:**\n- Expose `valid_at_from` and `valid_at_to` as optional MCP parameters on `memory_search`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Consolidation impact — no changes required\n\nThe LLM consolidation pipeline operates on episodes (butler runtime session transcripts). Temporal facts are written directly by health butler diet tools, not through episode consolidation. The consolidator's `store_fact` calls never provide `valid_at`, so they always produce property facts with standard supersession behavior.\n\n**Subtle edge case:** If the consolidator extracts a property fact with the same key as an existing temporal fact, the spec says they coexist (property and temporal facts coexist per spec line 66). This is already handled correctly by the proposed supersession logic: the new property fact (valid_at=NULL) will supersede any existing active property fact (valid_at=NULL) for the same key, but leave temporal facts (valid_at!=NULL) untouched.\n\n**Prompt guidance:** The consolidation prompt should note that temporal predicates (meal_breakfast, etc.) should NOT be included in consolidation output — those facts live as temporal sequences, not property updates. This is a prompt change, not a code change.\n\n---\n\n### 6. EmbeddingEngine access for health diet tools\n\n**Current state:** `roster/health/tools/diet.py` writes to a dedicated `meals` table. After migration to facts, it needs to call `store_fact()` which requires an `EmbeddingEngine`.\n\n**Cleanest import path:**\n```python\nfrom butlers.modules.memory.storage import store_fact\nfrom butlers.modules.memory.embedding import EmbeddingEngine\n```\n\n**Wiring pattern (follow MemoryModule's approach):**\n1. `HealthModule` grows `_embedding_engine` attribute and `_get_embedding_engine()` method\n2. `_get_embedding_engine()` lazy-loads via `from butlers.modules.memory.tools import get_embedding_engine; return get_embedding_engine()`\n3. `register_tools()` in `tools.py` passes `module._get_embedding_engine()` into diet tool calls\n4. `meal_log()`, `meal_history()`, `nutrition_summary()` accept `embedding_engine` parameter where needed\n\n**Note:** Only `meal_log` needs `embedding_engine` (for the INSERT via `store_fact`). `meal_history` and `nutrition_summary` query facts but don't write, so they use `pool` only.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of gaps not covered by existing sibling beads\n\n| Gap | Notes |\n|-----|-------|\n| Migration: `valid_at` column + index on `facts` table | Must be part of bu-axm.5 or a new migration bead |\n| Migration: `is_temporal` column on `predicate_registry` | Not covered by any existing bead |\n| `memory_search` `valid_at` range filter | Not covered by any existing bead |\n| Health butler `HealthModule` embedding_engine wiring | Part of diet-as-facts bead (not yet created) |\n| `diet.py` rewrite: meal tools as fact wrappers | Not covered by any existing bead |\n"}
